<h2 id="examples-of-relative-pronouns-from-papygreek-corpus">Examples of
relative pronouns from PapyGreek corpus</h2>
<ol type="1">
<li>κόμισαι παρὰ τοῦ ἀποδιδόντος σοι τὸ ἐπιστόλιον καλάθιον ἐν
<strong>ᾧ</strong> <strong>ὃ</strong> ἐὰν εὑρίσκεις αὐτὸ ἀντιγράψεις
μοι.<br>
(kómisai parà toû apodidóntos soi tò epistólion kaláthion en
<strong>hô(i) hò</strong> eàn heurískeis autò antigrápseis moi.)<br>
<em>Receive from the one who brings this letter to you a basket and
write back to me what you find in it.</em><br>
<a href="https://papygreek.com/text/33027">p.mich.8.481</a>, 5-8
(sentence 3), transl. White (1986) p.177.</li>
</ol>
